# Pointer Arithmetic in Embedded C

## Overview
This section contains programs related to pointer arithmetic and memory traversal in Embedded C.

## Concepts Covered
- Pointer movement
- Address increment behavior
- Array access using pointers
- Modifying arrays using pointer arithmetic
- Relationship between indexing and pointers

## Why It Matters in Embedded Systems
Pointer arithmetic is important for:
- buffer handling
- memory traversal
- communication data processing
- register block access
- low-level firmware operations

Understanding pointer arithmetic helps in efficient memory handling and firmware development.
